00:00:22.130 --> 00:00:23.460
journals too.

00:00:23.460 --> 00:00:28.279
Scientists from the University of Waterloo
even put together a Bullshit Receptivity Scale,

00:00:28.279 --> 00:00:31.509
designed to gauge how likely people are to
fall for it.

00:00:31.509 --> 00:00:35.690
According to Princeton Philosopher Harry Frankfurt,
though BS can take many forms, there is one

00:00:35.690 --> 00:00:42.030
particular type of bull-patty statement that
we seem to fall for the most; pseudoprofound-bullshit.

00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:45.900
This is made up of statements that lack true
meaning - empty statements that are designed

00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:48.530
to impress, but don’t really get at anything.

00:00:48.530 --> 00:00:52.580
J: Manure peddlers of the pseudotype variety
may or may not be aware of the truth - they

00:00:52.580 --> 00:00:55.900
may believe what they’re saying even though
they are totally clueless.

00:00:55.900 --> 00:01:00.480
This is different from liars in that liars
are aware of the truth and intentionally manipulate

00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:02.230
it to deceive someone.

00:01:02.230 --> 00:01:06.000
Pseudo profound statements are also different
from nonsense, because nonsense statements,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:10.320
on their surface, are obviously not communicating
anything - they may lack proper syntax and

00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:11.320
structure.

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:14.500
L: Whereas male bovine excrement seems - on
the surface - to make sense.

00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:18.760
In their article published in the journal
Judgment And Decision Making, researchers

00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:20.930
give some examples of pseudoprofound-bullshit.

00:01:20.930 --> 00:01:24.550
I’m including one of them for you to test
if you can sniff it out.

00:01:24.550 --> 00:01:25.550
Reaaaady….

00:01:25.550 --> 00:01:26.550
J: Yep, bring it on.

